      (Lenny's Newsletter)
    - Capture one content idea per day immediately when it hits - don't judge or workshop it, just write it down. Most creators experience dozens of post-worthy moments but let them fade by not capturing them instantly.
      (Hypefury)
    - Stop overplanning content strategy - publish first, refine later. Graham Mann spent 2 weeks planning before posting and got zero growth, then succeeded by publishing immediately and iterating. -> https://grahammann.net/blog/how-to-grow-on-x-twitter-2026
      (Hypefury)
    - Write only about topics you've spent 2+ years working on or struggling with. This limitation actually frees you because you're remembering instead of researching - the thinking is already done.
      (Hypefury)
    - Convert daily moments into content ideas: when you think 'I wish someone told me this sooner', when you explain something to a friend, or when you disagree with online advice - all are posts waiting to happen.
      (Hypefury)

